descript.abstract: This polygon dataset shows information regarding the 2007 Census of Agriculture in the United States. This map layer portrays a selected set of information that was collected for the 2007 Census of Agriculture by the National Agricultural Statistics Service, U.S. Department of Agriculture. There are 25 categories of data which include information about farms, crops, livestock, values of products, and farm operator characteristics. This is a replacement for the June 2005 Agriculture Census of the United States 2002 map layer.
descript.purpose: This dataset is intended for researchers, students, and policy makers for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data.
descript.supplinf: The data should be displayed and analyzed at scales appropriate for 1:2,000,000-scale data.

attracc.attraccr: Attribute information remains the same as given by the author of the data. However, when information is missing or ambiguous, the GIS Information Systems Center at Tufts University researches other metadata sources for explanations. If sufficient information is unavailable, "unknown attribute" is given as the definition. If the attribute has been created through a geoprocessing function, "geoprocessed identifier" is given. If the attribute is known, but the values are not, "unknown" is given for values. Features' units of measurement are determined if not already given.

dataqual.logic: The map layer was checked for topological consistency using the ArcGIS command BUILD. No other checks for logical consistency were performed on this map layer.
dataqual.complete: This map layer includes 25 categories from the National Agricultural Statistics Service, U.S. Department of Agriculture's 2002 Census of Agriculture data. It is based on county data for all 50 States.

procstep.procdesc:
The following edits were done to ATLAS-2000CNTY which is a map layer containing 2000 county boundaries for the United States. Puerto Rico, U.S. Virgin Islands, and the Great Lakes and other waterbody areas were deleted. Some of the county level boundaries were modified to show geographic areas for which 2002 agricultural census statistics are reported. Certain individual counties were assigned the FIPS code of a designated adjacent or surrounding county. Counties were aggregated by dissolving boundaries between counties which had the same county FIPS code. The following is a list of counties with modified boundaries. The Agricultural Census county codes and associated (=) U.S. county FIPS codes are identified below. >02010 = 02013, 02016, 02050, 02060, 02070, 02150, 02164, 02180, 02185, > 02188, 02270 >02020 = 02020, 02170, 02261 >02090 = 02090, 02068, 02240, 02290 >02110 = 02100, 02130, 02110, 02201, 02220, 02232, 02280, 02282 >15009 = 15009, 15005 >24033 = 24033, 11001 >24005 = 24005, 24510 >29189 = 29189, 29510 >51003 = 51003, 51540 >51005 = 51005, 51560, 51580 >51015 = 51015, 51790, 51820 >51019 = 51059, 51515 >51031 = 51031, 51680 >51041 = 51041, 51570 >51059 = 51059, 51510, 51600, 51610 >51069 = 51069, 51840 >51077 = 51077, 51640 >51081 = 51081, 51595 >51087 = 51087, 51760 >51089 = 51089, 51690 >51095 = 51095, 51830 >51121 = 51121, 51750 >51143 = 51143, 51590 >51149 = 51149, 51670, 51730 >51153 = 51153, 51683, 51685 >51161 = 51161, 51770, 51775 >51163 = 51163, 51530, 51678 >51165 = 51165, 51660 >51175 = 51175, 51620 >51177 = 51177, 51630 >51191 = 51191, 51520 >51195 = 51195, 51720 >51199 = 51199, 51650, 51700, 51735 >51550 = 51550, 51740 >51810 = 51810, 51710 > In the AG-CENSUS2002 database files the fields flagged with C (confidential, data withheld to avoid disclosing information for individual farms) were changed from 0 to -9999.
The database files from AG-CENSUS2002 were joined to the edited county boundaries to create the final map layer.
